hypothesis: Experiment→lesson loss drops from 89% (S347) to ~80-85% system-wide due to targeted harvests S353-S358 in history, game-theory, and statistics. Harvested domains should show stable conversion above 0%.
method: Scanned experiments/ directory (526 JSON files across 44 domains, excluding children/merge-reports/integration-log), memory/lessons/ (595 files), and principles.md (173 principles). Matched experiments to lessons via domain-path citations in lesson files. Same methodology as S347 baseline.

measured.note: Conversion improved +3.4pp. Still dominant bottleneck but trending correct direction. 55 new experiments since S347, 24 new citations.
NEW FINDING: Promotion rate DECLINED. Lessons grew 30.8% (455→595) but principles grew only 1.8% (170→173). Principle extraction is falling behind — new bottleneck emerging.

history.verdict: NO CHANGE — harvest produced L-590/L-591 but they cite IS harvest experiments, not history experiments directly. Citation chain doesn't link back to original domain.

new_high_performers_since_s347.note: 7 exp, 5 cited — DOMEX lanes drove conversion

volume_conversion_paradox.finding: DOMEX lanes are the primary mechanism driving experiment→lesson conversion. Domains that received DOMEX attention show strong conversion; domains without DOMEX lanes remain at 0%. The harvest campaign improved game-theory but failed on history because harvest citations link to IS domain, not source domain.

new_bottleneck.cause: Lesson production (30.8% growth) outpaces principle extraction (1.8% growth). 140 new lessons since S347 but only 3 new principles.
new_bottleneck.implication: If trend continues, knowledge accumulates without distillation. Principles become stale relative to lesson base.
new_bottleneck.recommended_action: Run principles-dedup periodic with extraction focus: scan recent 50 lessons for recurring patterns that lack P-NNN entries.

expect_diff.surprise: Lesson→principle decline was not predicted. History 0% persistence despite harvest was not predicted.

verdict: PARTIAL — experiment→lesson improved +3.4pp (harvest campaign works for game-theory, marginal for statistics, fails for history). New bottleneck found: lesson→principle promotion declining. DOMEX lanes are the proven conversion mechanism.
next_steps: History domain: harvest methodology needs to cite original domain experiments, not just IS wrapper
Principle extraction: run targeted principle synthesis from L-550+ lessons (140 lessons, only 3 principles)
Rerun at S385 (20 sessions) to measure principle extraction after targeted intervention
